The Nigerian Communication Commission, (NCC) in partnership with stakeholders celebrated World Telecommunications and Information Society Day (WTSID).
The WTSID is an annual event that helps to create awareness about the benefits of telecommunications. The commemoration also aimed at bridging the digital divide.
READ ALSO: NCC alert car owners to new trick of hackers
According to NCC, the objective of this year’s celebration, “Digital Technologies for Older Persons and Healthy Ageing”, is aimed at ensuring technology remains socially inclusive for the elderly and the aged.
It also aimed at ensuring that older people utilize digital technologies to maintain healthy and productive lives.
The 2022 World Telecommunications and Information Society Day was celebrated by NCC with fanfare at its corporate head office in Abuja.
